'''
print('10 Real Finance Example (Small)')
'''
Imagine this DataFrame:

```python'''
data = {
    "Fund": ["Equity", "Debt", "Liquid", "Equity", "Debt"],
    "NAV": [150.5, 105.2, 10.45, 151.3, 105.7],
    "Units": [100, 200, 500, 150, 180]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)
'''```

### âœ” Calculate value of each holding

```python'''
df["Value"] = df["NAV"] * df["Units"]
print(df)
'''```

### âœ” Total portfolio value

```python'''
print("Total Value:", df["Value"].sum())
'''```

### âœ” Group by fund type (SQL GROUP BY)

```python'''
print(df.groupby("Fund")["Value"].sum())
'''```'''
print('5ï¸âƒ£ Reading Excel Files')
